A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing Mr. John W. Mixon and dedicating a building in his honor; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Mr. John W. Mixon has long been recognized by the citizens of this state for
4 the vital role that he has played in leadership and his deep personal commitment to the
5 welfare of the citizens of Georgia; and
6 WHEREAS, Mr. Mixon began his career as a conservation stalwart in 1961 as a forest
7 technician with the Georgia Forestry Commission and served as the head of the commission's
8 nationally recognized Urban Forestry Program; and
9 WHEREAS, he worked to accelerate wood energy promotions by conducting demonstrations
10 at public schools, prisons, hospitals, and other institutions to show how wood materials could
11 replace expensive fuels; and
12 WHEREAS, Mr. Mixon was named commissioner of the Georgia Forestry Commission in
13 1983 and during his tenure as commissioner he oversaw great conservation efforts, including
14 a record number of trees planted in a single season with 433,000 acres of pine trees and the
