15 establishment of the Flint River Nursery which was designed to produce 50 million
16 seedlings; and
17 WHEREAS, his leadership was instrumental in the passage of numerous laws relating to
18 forest conservation, including laws that required a permit for outdoor burning and provided
19 for prescribed burning for forest management; and
20 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments and
21 contributions of this remarkable and distinguished Georgian be recognized appropriately by
22 dedicating a building in his honor.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED AND ENACTED BY THE GENERAL
24 ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA that the Georgia Forestry Commission building located in Dry
25 Branch, Georgia, is dedicated as the John W. Mixon Georgia Forestry Building.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Georgia Building Authority is authorized and
27 directed to erect and maintain appropriate signs dedicating the John W. Mixon Georgia
28 Forestry Building to be funded from the budget of the Georgia Forestry Commission.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
30 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the
31 Georgia Forestry Commission and Mr. John W. Mixon.
